  "grammarNote": {
    "title": "The Imperfect: How Things Were",
    "explanation": "Il n'y avait pas d'électricité. On cherchait du bois. — notice the endings: avait, cherchait. These describe how things USED TO BE, not a single event.\n\nCompare: a disparu (passé composé — one event) vs. cherchait (imparfait — ongoing state). Different pasts.\n\nRe-read and separate -ait endings from a + [past verb]. Which describe a background state? Which describe a completed event?"
